comment: Not a huge fan of sour mashes. Notes of tar and baking spices are immediate. Long lasting mild sawdust flavor.
Just got 2 ounces by the mail today, paid 60 bucks for it, i've tried it before, it's a damn fine whiskey.
This is the best.  If you can find it, drink it.
Best bourbon I have ever had.
Well balanced fruity and oak.  Definitely not over oaked but lots of character.

Nose: Toffee 
Palate: Spicy, leather, old, red wine-ish.

Oaky, sweet, vanilla.  Very complex. Had this on a cruise, and my bartender gave it to us as part of a pappy van winkle flight.  Unfortunately, I didn't make detailed tasting notes, so I'm doing this based off of memory. Get this if you can!
